eq20\). conf.level = 0.95) This test has a 0.95 confidence level which corresponds to 1‚àíŒ±. ¬†¬†¬†¬†Press Enter to run the code if you have typed it in yourself. You can also click here to view the output. ¬†‚Ä¶¬† Click to View Output. Wilcoxon signed rank test with continuity correction This reports on the type of test performed. The phrase ‚Äúwith continuity correction‚Äù implies the normal approximation was used when calculating the p-value of the test. data: mtcars$mpg This print-out reminds us that the mpg column of the mtcars data was used as ‚ÄúY‚Äù in the test. V = 249, The test statistic of the test. ¬†p-value = 0.7863 The p-value of the test. alternative hypothesis: true location is not equal to 20 The words ‚Äúnot equal‚Äù tell us this was a two-sided test. Had it been a one-sided test, either the word ‚Äúless‚Äù or the word ‚Äúgreater‚Äù would have appeared instead of ‚Äúnot equal.‚Äù

